        <span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 12px;">Streetscape Improvement Project</span><br />
        In the Fall of 2007, the North 22nd Street Commercial District was selected to receive a grant from the Restore Program which is part of the NTI Bond program specifically designed to help improve the infrastructure on commercial corridors. This grant provided funds to hire KS Engineering to design and cost out a complete renovation of the entire commercial corridor infrastructure which would include new sidewalks, trees, street and pedestrian lights, and gateways to the commercial corridor. It also included money to start up and complete some of these improvements. There have been five meetings to date that have discussed ideas and design sample boards for selection by the merchants on the corridors affected. Now we are at a point of selecting what is the most critical improvement that is needed on the corridor that will be covered by the available funds. We will make this selection early 2009 with a project completion date in the fall of 2009.
        </td>
