                <span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 12px;">Façade Improvement Project</span><br />
                Initially, all commercial corridors were only to receive a streetscape grant. However the Commerce department proposed an additional grant to encourage beatification and rehabilitation of existing store fronts. The idea was to implement a contiguous uniform façade design on two blocks of the commercial corridor. The merchants would have to buy in to this program sharing a percentage of the costs along with agreeing to the façade guidelines. This would compliment the infrastructure improvements giving the commercial corridor a bright new look. A proposal was submitted to Commerce that would use this grant to treat 52 facades which would include new quarter barrel awnings with signage, removing old awnings and signage, new see through security gates that allows the interior of stores to be seen giving a more inviting look at night, new windows or window treatment, store front painting, and bay treatment and repair. Some buildings need major work and others very little. We are eagerly waiting for the awarding of this grant.            
